{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778377764366,"sessionID":"ses_1f0743276ffe7I5osG2ZI7mNhP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_jpxJ1E28nvn8FZQ8kxFiJnlw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/1.2.5.3","format":"text","timeout":30},"output":"ENZYME - 1.2.5.3 aerobic carbon monoxide dehydrogenase\n\n \n\n\n    \n        \n    \n    ENZYME\n    \n        \n            \n                 \n                Home\n            \n            \n                 \n                Browse\n                \n                    by classes\n                    by subclasses\n                    by subsubclasses\n                \n            \n            \n                 \n                Search\n                \n                    by EC number\n                    by name\n                    by chemical compound\n                    by comment\n                \n            \n            \n                 \n                Documentation\n                \n                    User Manual\n                    Access to ENZYME\n                \n            \n            \n                 \n                Downloads\n            \n            \n                 \n                Contact\n            \n        \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n    \nENZYME entry: EC 1.2.5.3\nPURL: https://purl.expasy.org/enzyme/EC/1.2.5.3\n\n\n\nAccepted Name\naerobic carbon monoxide dehydrogenase\n\nAlternative Name(s)\nmolybdoenzyme carbon monoxide dehydrogenase\nReaction catalysed\nCO + a quinone + H2O = a quinol + CO2\nComment(s)\nThis enzyme, found in carboxydotrophic bacteria, catalyzes the\n    oxidation of CO to CO2 under aerobic conditions.\nThe enzyme belongs to the xanthine oxidoreductase family.\nThe CO2 that is produced is assimilated by the Calvin-Benson-Basham\n    cycle, while the electrons are transferred to a quinone via the FAD\n    site, and continue through the electron transfer chain to a dioxygen\n    terminal acceptor. cf. EC 1.2.7.4.\n\nCross-references\nRhea expert-curated reactions1.2.5.3\nExplorEnz1.2.5.3\nIUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature1.2.5.3\nUniProtKB/Swiss-Prot\nP19919,&nbsp;DCML_AFIC5P19916,&nbsp;DCML_AFICRP19913,&nbsp;DCML_HYDPS\nP19920,&nbsp;DCMM_AFIC5P19917,&nbsp;DCMM_AFICRP19914,&nbsp;DCMM_HYDPS\nP19921,&nbsp;DCMS_AFIC5P19918,&nbsp;DCMS_AFICRP19915,&nbsp;DCMS_HYDPS\n\n\nBRENDA1.2.5.3\nMetaCyc1.2.5.3\nKEGG Ligand Database for Enzyme Nomenclature1.2.5.3\nMEDLINEFind literature relating to 1.2.5.3\n\nView entry in original ENZYME format\nView entry in raw text format (no links)\nAll UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot \nentries referenced\nin this entry, with possibility to download in different formats, align etc.\n\nAll ENZYME / UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries corresponding to 1.2.5.-\nAll ENZYME / UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries corresponding to 1.2.-.-\nAll ENZYME / UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries corresponding to 1.-.-.-\n\n\n    \n    \n    \n\t    \n            \n\t\t\n\t\t\n           Expasy \n\t\t   is operated by the SIB Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics\n\t\t   \n\t\t   Terms of Use\n           |\n           Privacy policy\n\t    \n\t    \n\t        Back to the top","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/1.2.5.3 (text/html; charset=UTF-8)","time":{"start":1778377761462,"end":1778377764364}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ae37ce44f1ec76c0169ffe42031688194b96ca53e63a5520e"}},"id":"prt_e0f931df40013YycYgzHGaXyu6","sessionID":"ses_1f0743276ffe7I5osG2ZI7mNhP","messageID":"msg_e0f93117e001mdM4DzD1827Fmq"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778377764370,"sessionID":"ses_1f0743276ffe7I5osG2ZI7mNhP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_H63rkTFIs41h42hgBhoUozhw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/1.2.7.4","format":"text","timeout":30},"output":"ENZYME - 1.2.7.4 anaerobic carbon-monoxide dehydrogenase\n\n \n\n\n    \n        \n    \n    ENZYME\n    \n        \n            \n                 \n                Home\n            \n            \n                 \n                Browse\n                \n                    by classes\n                    by subclasses\n                    by subsubclasses\n                \n            \n            \n                 \n                Search\n                \n                    by EC number\n                    by name\n                    by chemical compound\n                    by comment\n                \n            \n            \n                 \n                Documentation\n                \n                    User Manual\n                    Access to ENZYME\n                \n            \n            \n                 \n                Downloads\n            \n            \n                 \n                Contact\n            \n        \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n    \nENZYME entry: EC 1.2.7.4\nPURL: https://purl.expasy.org/enzyme/EC/1.2.7.4\n\n\n\nAccepted Name\nanaerobic carbon-monoxide dehydrogenase\n\nAlternative Name(s)\ncarbon-monoxide dehydrogenase (ferredoxin)\nNi-CODH\nReaction catalysed\nCO + 2 oxidized [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin] + H2O = 2 reduced [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin] + CO2 + 2 H(+)\nComment(s)\nThis prokaryotic enzyme catalyzes the reversible reduction of CO2 to\n    CO.\nThe electrons are transferred to redox proteins such as ferredoxin.\nIn purple sulfur bacteria and methanogenic archaea it catalyzes the\n    oxidation of CO to CO2, which is incorporated by the Calvin-Benson-\n    Basham cycle or released, respectively.\nIn acetogenic and sulfate-reducing microbes it catalyzes the\n    reduction of CO2 to CO, which is incorporated into acetyl CoA by\n    EC 2.3.1.169, with which the enzyme forms a tight complex in those\n    organisms.\nIn purple sulfur bacteria the enzyme forms complexes with the Ni-Fe-S\n    protein EC 1.12.7.2 which catalyze the overall reaction: CO + H2O =\n    CO2 + H2. cf. EC 1.2.5.3.\nFormerly EC 1.2.99.2.\n\nCross-references\nRhea expert-curated reactions1.2.7.4\nExplorEnz1.2.7.4\nIUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature1.2.7.4\nUniProtKB/Swiss-Prot\nO29165,&nbsp;ACDA1_ARCFUQ8TRZ4,&nbsp;ACDA1_METACQ46G04,&nbsp;ACDA1_METBF\nQ8TXF7,&nbsp;ACDA1_METKAQ49161,&nbsp;ACDA1_METMAQ08368,&nbsp;ACDA1_METTE\nO30274,&nbsp;ACDA2_ARCFUQ8TJC6,&nbsp;ACDA2_METACQ49163,&nbsp;ACDA2_METMA\nQ9C4Z4,&nbsp;ACDA2_METTEQ8THW2,&nbsp;ACDA3_METACQ12XL7,&nbsp;ACDA_METBU\nQ57617,&nbsp;ACDA_METJAP26692,&nbsp;ACDA_METSHO27743,&nbsp;ACDA_METTH\nP59934,&nbsp;COOS1_CARHZQ8TKW2,&nbsp;COOS1_METACQ8Q0L5,&nbsp;COOS1_METMA\nQ9F8A8,&nbsp;COOS2_CARHZQ8TR73,&nbsp;COOS2_METACQ8PUN1,&nbsp;COOS2_METMA\nO28429,&nbsp;COOS_ARCFUQ58138,&nbsp;COOS_METJAQ8TXX3,&nbsp;COOS_METKA\nP31896,&nbsp;COOS_RHORUP27989,&nbsp;DCMB_NEOTH\n\nBRENDA1.2.7.4\nMetaCyc1.2.7.4\nKEGG Ligand Database for Enzyme Nomenclature1.2.7.4\nMEDLINEFind literature relating to 1.2.7.4\n\nView entry in original ENZYME format\nView entry in raw text format (no links)\nAll UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot \nentries referenced\nin this entry, with possibility to download in different formats, align etc.\n\nAll ENZYME / UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries corresponding to 1.2.7.-\nAll ENZYME / UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries corresponding to 1.2.-.-\nAll ENZYME / UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot entries corresponding to 1.-.-.-\n\n\n    \n    \n    \n\t    \n            \n\t\t\n\t\t\n           Expasy \n\t\t   is operated by the SIB Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics\n\t\t   \n\t\t   Terms of Use\n           |\n           Privacy policy\n\t    \n\t    \n\t        Back to the top","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https